---
title: "NIST AI Risk Management Framework — a continuous loop, not a one-time checklist"
config:
  theme: base
  themeVariables:
    primaryColor: "#a5d8ff"
    primaryBorderColor: "#4a9eed"
    lineColor: "#555"
    fontSize: "16px"
  flowchart:
    htmlLabels: true
    curve: basis
    nodeSpacing: 60
    rankSpacing: 70
---
flowchart TB
    MAP["<b>Map</b><br><span style='font-size:13px;color:#6d28d9'>Understand context and spot the risks</span><br><span style='font-size:12px;color:#444'>What is this for, what could go wrong?</span>"]
    MEASURE["<b>Measure</b><br><span style='font-size:13px;color:#6d28d9'>Assess and track the risks with evidence</span><br><span style='font-size:12px;color:#444'>How big is each risk?</span>"]
    MANAGE["<b>Manage</b><br><span style='font-size:13px;color:#6d28d9'>Act on the risks</span><br><span style='font-size:12px;color:#444'>What do we actually do?</span>"]
    GOVERN["<b>Govern</b><br><span style='font-size:13px;color:#6d28d9'>Set culture, rules, responsibilities</span><br><span style='font-size:12px;color:#444'>Cross-cutting: ties the other three together</span>"]

    MAP -->|then| MEASURE
    MEASURE -->|then| MANAGE
    MANAGE ==>|"loop back as systems and risks change"| MAP

    GOVERN -. "holds the whole loop together" .-> MAP
    GOVERN -.-> MEASURE
    GOVERN -.-> MANAGE

    classDef loop fill:#a5d8ff,stroke:#4a9eed,stroke-width:2px,color:#000;
    classDef center fill:#fff3bf,stroke:#f59e0b,stroke-width:3px,color:#000;

    class MAP,MEASURE,MANAGE loop;
    class GOVERN center;
